1
00:00:37,537 --> 00:00:39,330
I guess we share a special relationship.

2
00:00:42,167 --> 00:00:43,460
You and I.

3
00:00:46,504 --> 00:00:47,672
Listen.

4
00:00:48,840 --> 00:00:50,258
We both like Lee Sol's paintings.

5
00:00:51,885 --> 00:00:53,052
Twenty-seven thousand.

6
00:00:53,136 --> 00:00:55,138
Twenty-nine. Thirty thousand dollars.

7
00:00:55,221 --> 00:00:56,347
Hey, mister!

8
00:00:56,681 --> 00:01:00,351
That artwork you just bid for,
please yield it to me.

9
00:01:03,021 --> 00:01:04,606
We live in the same apartment.

10
00:01:06,357 --> 00:01:07,734
Do you work here?

11
00:01:08,610 --> 00:01:10,111
May I help you?

12
00:01:10,945 --> 00:01:13,239
The artist I like is an acquaintance
of yours.

13
00:01:13,490 --> 00:01:14,866
Are we meeting an artist?

14
00:01:15,200 --> 00:01:16,326
We're meeting a collector.

15
00:01:16,451 --> 00:01:19,037
It's Cha Si-an of White Ocean.

16
00:01:20,997 --> 00:01:22,123
What?

17
00:01:24,459 --> 00:01:27,545
The jacket. We even have
the same jacket, remember?

18
00:01:29,672 --> 00:01:30,799
Wear this.

19
00:01:31,466 --> 00:01:33,384
Although that jacket led to a problem,

20
00:01:33,468 --> 00:01:35,053
this isn't a coincidence.

21
00:01:35,345 --> 00:01:36,596
It must be fate.

22
00:01:53,321 --> 00:01:54,739
Here you are.

23
00:01:55,740 --> 00:01:57,784
-Thank you.
-Sure.

24
00:01:58,451 --> 00:01:59,661
What about Ms. Sung?

25
00:02:00,036 --> 00:02:01,371
She went to the workshop.

26
00:02:01,496 --> 00:02:04,207
They said they need to deliver some wood,
but no one's at the workshop.

27
00:02:04,290 --> 00:02:05,500
So?

28
00:02:05,959 --> 00:02:09,087
I didn't ask her to go.
Ms. Sung said she'd go herself.

29
00:02:09,712 --> 00:02:12,590
She should be a part of this meeting.
Why go to the workshop?

30
00:02:12,715 --> 00:02:14,342
Is she not feeling well?

31
00:02:15,426 --> 00:02:17,679
Ms. Sung looked troubled today.

32
00:02:18,555 --> 00:02:20,515
What time is the meeting

33
00:02:20,723 --> 00:02:21,641
with Mr. Cha and Ms. Choi?

34
00:02:22,183 --> 00:02:23,351
It's at 2 p.m.

35
00:02:23,476 --> 00:02:26,146
-Then at 1 p.m. in the parking lot--
-Actually,

36
00:02:27,564 --> 00:02:29,440
I have a meeting outside
prior to that one.

37
00:02:29,524 --> 00:02:31,651
I'll head to her studio from there.

38
00:02:34,362 --> 00:02:38,158
If Si-an can't make you smile, that means

39
00:02:38,741 --> 00:02:41,578
you're actually really sick.

40
00:02:45,582 --> 00:02:47,834
It was the first time I saw Ms. Sung
without a smile.

41
00:02:48,042 --> 00:02:50,003
She was smiling every time I saw her.

42
00:02:51,045 --> 00:02:53,047
So I thought she was my fan.

43
00:02:57,385 --> 00:02:59,721
-Please continue with the meeting.
-What?

44
00:03:00,722 --> 00:03:02,432
-Ryan.
-Hey.

45
00:03:06,019 --> 00:03:07,353
Is he going to see Ms. Sung?

46
00:03:18,740 --> 00:03:20,867
She should've told me if she was sick.

47
00:03:27,582 --> 00:03:29,626
FURNITURE WORKSHOP

48
00:03:53,316 --> 00:03:54,609
Ms. Sung?

49
00:04:24,847 --> 00:04:26,182
Ms. Sung.

50
00:04:29,644 --> 00:04:30,895
Director Gold.

51
00:04:37,026 --> 00:04:39,070
I didn't want to ask you.

52
00:04:40,238 --> 00:04:42,407
I really didn't want to ask you this.

53
00:04:48,496 --> 00:04:50,331
What was so hard for you?

54
00:04:52,208 --> 00:04:53,793
About being in a fake relationship
with me.

55
00:05:02,093 --> 00:05:03,928
Did you hate it that much?

56
00:05:10,852 --> 00:05:12,061
Yes.

57
00:05:14,772 --> 00:05:16,733
What did you hate so much about it?

58
00:05:16,941 --> 00:05:18,943
I didn't call you every day

59
00:05:19,027 --> 00:05:20,737
or ask you to meet me.

60
00:05:22,030 --> 00:05:23,197
All you had to do

61
00:05:23,865 --> 00:05:25,700
was pretend for a short moment.

62
00:05:27,035 --> 00:05:28,286
Was it that hard

63
00:05:28,995 --> 00:05:30,246
and stressful for you?

64
00:05:36,252 --> 00:05:38,046
I was so excited and happy.

65
00:05:39,797 --> 00:05:42,216
-What was so--
-Because it was fake.

66
00:06:00,193 --> 00:06:01,903
I hated it because it was fake.

67
00:06:07,075 --> 00:06:08,659
I wanted to date you for real.

68
00:07:15,059 --> 00:07:16,269
Hello?

69
00:07:16,936 --> 00:07:18,271
Anyone here?

70
00:07:19,564 --> 00:07:22,024
Is anyone here? Excuse me.

71
00:07:28,990 --> 00:07:30,199
Hello?

72
00:07:33,619 --> 00:07:35,163
Is no one here?

73
00:08:29,550 --> 00:08:32,512
The exhibition is in two months,
so we're quite tight on schedule.

74
00:08:33,304 --> 00:08:35,097
What will you be exhibiting?

75
00:08:35,348 --> 00:08:36,432
Here.

76
00:08:36,516 --> 00:08:38,601
ARTWORK OWNED BY CHA SI-AN

77
00:08:38,893 --> 00:08:41,312
Director Gold also likes this painting.

78
00:08:41,395 --> 00:08:42,647
There are nine paintings in total.

79
00:08:42,730 --> 00:08:44,398
I want to collect them all
and exhibit them.

80
00:08:48,027 --> 00:08:49,654
-Just a second. I'm sorry.
-Okay.

81
00:08:52,406 --> 00:08:54,659
No one's at the workshop,
so I'll just have to leave.

82
00:09:34,365 --> 00:09:35,950
-You must be hungry.
-That wasn't me.

83
00:09:36,033 --> 00:09:37,785
You're hungry even in this situation?

84
00:09:37,868 --> 00:09:39,287
I just said it wasn't me.

85
00:09:40,538 --> 00:09:43,249
My stomach's just digesting
because I drank coffee earlier.

86
00:09:48,379 --> 00:09:50,631
-Should we get something to eat?
-Yes.

87
00:10:10,943 --> 00:10:12,111
Wait.

88
00:10:17,908 --> 00:10:19,160
What's that?

89
00:10:20,036 --> 00:10:22,121
A flashlight. It's just a flashlight.

90
00:10:22,955 --> 00:10:25,082
-A flashlight?
-Yes.

91
00:10:26,334 --> 00:10:28,336
-It's pretty.
-Right?

92
00:10:37,178 --> 00:10:38,304
Editor Nam.

93
00:10:38,596 --> 00:10:41,474
You should've opened a bookstore,
not a publishing company.

94
00:10:43,601 --> 00:10:46,312
Moment magazines are right here.

95
00:10:46,646 --> 00:10:49,315
I was wondering why we had
a sudden increase in sales.

96
00:10:49,398 --> 00:10:51,609
It must be thanks to Director Gold.

97
00:10:52,526 --> 00:10:55,988
He really is just the right person
for Duk-mi.

98
00:10:57,323 --> 00:10:59,283
Mom, what about me?

99
00:10:59,575 --> 00:11:00,951
What do you mean?

100
00:11:01,410 --> 00:11:02,787
Wouldn't I be good for Duk-mi as well?

101
00:11:05,206 --> 00:11:06,332
That's a horrible joke...

102
00:11:10,836 --> 00:11:12,129
Eun-gi.

103
00:11:12,213 --> 00:11:13,631
I'm the only guy

104
00:11:14,924 --> 00:11:16,092
who knows Duk-mi

105
00:11:16,550 --> 00:11:18,094
better than herself.

106
00:11:31,273 --> 00:11:33,275
I went there to check the wood, though.

107
00:11:33,651 --> 00:11:36,195
I feel so guilty.

108
00:11:37,154 --> 00:11:39,740
Maybe we should've gone back
to her studio for the meeting.

109
00:11:40,157 --> 00:11:41,659
-Mr. Cha--
-What did you like about me?

110
00:11:41,784 --> 00:11:42,785
Pardon?

111
00:11:42,868 --> 00:11:44,370
When did you get excited and happy?

112
00:11:44,495 --> 00:11:46,580
I don't know what you mean.

113
00:11:48,791 --> 00:11:50,418
That's what you said earlier.

114
00:11:52,962 --> 00:11:55,297
I wonder when it all began.

115
00:11:56,632 --> 00:11:59,427
Was it when we took photos
of our fake relationship?

116
00:12:00,761 --> 00:12:01,679
Or was it

117
00:12:02,346 --> 00:12:04,223
at Mr. Roh's cabin?

118
00:12:04,974 --> 00:12:07,184
Or was it when you blindfolded me

119
00:12:07,268 --> 00:12:09,270
-at your place?
-Director Gold.

120
00:12:10,521 --> 00:12:12,231
Do you want gimbap?

121
00:12:12,481 --> 00:12:15,443
I'm craving gimbap because I didn't
get to have any last time.

122
00:12:15,526 --> 00:12:17,027
So why don't we eat gimbap?

123
00:12:17,111 --> 00:12:18,904
-Gimbap?
-Gimbap.

124
00:12:18,988 --> 00:12:20,698
-Cheongyang chili gimbap?
-Yes.

125
00:12:26,829 --> 00:12:28,080
Ta-da.

126
00:12:32,793 --> 00:12:34,170
By the way, it's spicy.

127
00:12:45,973 --> 00:12:48,267
Haven't you cleaned your place yet?

128
00:12:49,977 --> 00:12:51,604
-Are you cold?
-No, I'm fine.

129
00:12:54,440 --> 00:12:57,401
So I guess this is
the night view of Seoul.

130
00:12:57,693 --> 00:13:00,571
Isn't the night view a lot better
from your place?

131
00:13:02,740 --> 00:13:04,074
I'm not sure.

132
00:13:04,533 --> 00:13:08,078
To be honest, I moved here
because I also liked this view.

133
00:13:08,287 --> 00:13:09,497
It's a penthouse.

134
00:13:10,414 --> 00:13:11,707
A penthouse?

135
00:13:13,417 --> 00:13:14,627
Next time you move,

136
00:13:15,211 --> 00:13:17,213
you should get a place with an elevator.

137
00:13:19,048 --> 00:13:20,216
Do you want one?

138
00:13:21,175 --> 00:13:22,426
Why not? Try one.

139
00:13:23,761 --> 00:13:24,970
I'm sorry.

140
00:13:26,305 --> 00:13:27,306
It's okay.

141
00:13:27,389 --> 00:13:30,267
You already ruined
a handful of my clothes.

142
00:13:31,560 --> 00:13:32,478
Didn't I

143
00:13:33,270 --> 00:13:34,813
only ruin two?

144
00:13:36,357 --> 00:13:39,485
Why are you so bad with chopsticks
when you're Korean?

145
00:13:39,818 --> 00:13:42,696
What? I'm really good at using chopsticks.

146
00:13:43,405 --> 00:13:44,949
You must think you're good.

147
00:13:45,032 --> 00:13:47,243
-Are you good?
-I'm really good.

148
00:13:48,160 --> 00:13:50,371
-You call this good?
-Of course.

149
00:13:51,038 --> 00:13:53,040
Did that work back when you were abroad?

150
00:14:01,507 --> 00:14:03,717
-Go home safely, Editor Nam.
-Eun-gi.

151
00:14:07,137 --> 00:14:08,347
I'm...

152
00:14:09,515 --> 00:14:10,432
sorry.

153
00:14:11,892 --> 00:14:13,060
All of a sudden?

154
00:14:14,103 --> 00:14:15,187
About what?

155
00:14:15,479 --> 00:14:17,022
I didn't know.

156
00:14:18,315 --> 00:14:21,110
I can't believe I didn't know
my own son's feelings.

157
00:14:21,193 --> 00:14:24,029
But then again, I never really
raised you myself.

158
00:14:25,030 --> 00:14:27,449
If I knew you had feelings
for Duk-mi, I would've--

159
00:14:27,533 --> 00:14:28,534
Mom.

160
00:14:29,952 --> 00:14:31,745
I didn't know either.

161
00:14:36,250 --> 00:14:37,710
I found out pretty recently.

162
00:14:39,879 --> 00:14:41,130
I was stupid.

163
00:14:47,261 --> 00:14:50,264
So just root for me
instead of feeling sorry.

164
00:14:50,806 --> 00:14:51,724
Okay?

165
00:14:54,602 --> 00:14:55,853
I'll be off now.

166
00:15:08,240 --> 00:15:11,410
I'll talk to Ms. Choi and Mr. Cha
tomorrow and explain.

167
00:15:11,577 --> 00:15:12,745
Okay, Director Gold.

168
00:15:15,706 --> 00:15:17,708
-Ms. Sung.
-Yes, Director Gold?

169
00:15:19,460 --> 00:15:20,669
Duk-mi.

170
00:15:21,629 --> 00:15:23,464
Yes, Director Gold.

171
00:15:27,635 --> 00:15:31,305
We're in a relationship now, right?

172
00:15:31,764 --> 00:15:33,974
We're no longer faking it.
This is for real, right?

173
00:15:34,183 --> 00:15:37,144
In Korea, if you don't go out
with the person you kiss, you go to jail.

174
00:15:38,604 --> 00:15:40,481
Of course, we're in a relationship.

175
00:15:41,899 --> 00:15:44,443
It's just that you sounded
really formal just now.

176
00:15:46,904 --> 00:15:48,656
How about we call each other by our names?

177
00:15:50,074 --> 00:15:51,033
Ryan?

178
00:15:56,038 --> 00:15:57,289
Wait, that's a little...

179
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:01,877
I wonder if there's a friendly nickname
you can use.

180
00:16:01,961 --> 00:16:04,630
A friendly nickname? I could call you...

181
00:16:06,548 --> 00:16:07,967
Lion, that jerk.

182
00:16:14,765 --> 00:16:16,558
I'll just call you more comfortably
from now on.

183
00:16:17,810 --> 00:16:18,686
I'll see you tomorrow.

184
00:17:00,686 --> 00:17:02,146
I hated it because it was fake.

185
00:17:05,149 --> 00:17:06,984
I wanted to date you for real.

186
00:17:24,376 --> 00:17:26,503
It'd be nice if I could have
a video footage of my memory.

187
00:17:27,379 --> 00:17:29,298
I want to keep replaying it.

188
00:17:30,466 --> 00:17:32,176
I want to take a screenshot of it.

189
00:17:33,135 --> 00:17:36,013
I'll screen capture it,
photoshop it, and create a GIF.

190
00:18:04,333 --> 00:18:06,251
THE ROAD TO SI-AN

191
00:18:06,335 --> 00:18:09,254
Latte, that person you like
might not be toying with your heart.

192
00:18:09,338 --> 00:18:11,131
Maybe that person just took a step back

193
00:18:11,215 --> 00:18:14,384
because she didn't know how you felt
and didn't want to get hurt.

194
00:18:16,386 --> 00:18:17,471
To be honest,

195
00:18:17,930 --> 00:18:19,473
that's what I did.

196
00:18:20,849 --> 00:18:24,061
So try mustering up your courage
one more time. Good luck.

197
00:18:44,373 --> 00:18:47,084
Thank you, The Road to Si-an.

198
00:19:00,514 --> 00:19:02,683
-Seon-ju.
-Duk-mi, look at this.

199
00:19:02,975 --> 00:19:04,393
Seung-min bought me a purse.

200
00:19:04,643 --> 00:19:05,727
Really? It's pretty.

201
00:19:05,811 --> 00:19:08,272
He placed it in a locker
as a surprise gift.

202
00:19:08,355 --> 00:19:10,357
Really? That's so clever of him.

203
00:19:10,440 --> 00:19:12,609
I wouldn't be with him if he weren't.

204
00:19:12,943 --> 00:19:15,154
-My husband--
-I'm dating the Lion.

205
00:19:17,156 --> 00:19:18,907
-What?
-I told you

206
00:19:18,991 --> 00:19:20,993
that he seemed to like me, too.

207
00:19:23,871 --> 00:19:27,541
I want to know what happened
in detail, so spill.

208
00:19:38,010 --> 00:19:39,344
"I wanted to date you for real."

209
00:19:41,597 --> 00:19:43,682
Gosh, you're all grown up now.

210
00:19:46,435 --> 00:19:47,895
-Duk-mi.
-Yes?

211
00:19:47,978 --> 00:19:50,355
-Have you told Eun-gi?
-No, not yet.

212
00:19:50,439 --> 00:19:52,107
Then let's not tell him
for the time being.

213
00:19:52,191 --> 00:19:53,442
Why not?

214
00:19:54,067 --> 00:19:57,654
Once he finds out,
he'll tell your parents.

215
00:19:57,863 --> 00:19:59,281
Are you sure you can handle that?

216
00:20:01,200 --> 00:20:03,243
No, I can't. It can't happen.

217
00:20:03,327 --> 00:20:05,454
I shouldn't tell Eun-gi just yet.

218
00:20:05,537 --> 00:20:07,331
You shouldn't tell him, either.

219
00:20:09,249 --> 00:20:13,378
Ju-hyeok, can I get
and iced latte with condensed milk?

220
00:20:13,462 --> 00:20:14,546
Takeout!

221
00:20:22,930 --> 00:20:24,264
Have you had your coffee yet?

222
00:20:24,473 --> 00:20:25,891
I got this for you.

223
00:20:25,974 --> 00:20:28,268
Iced Americano with an extra shot.

224
00:20:28,352 --> 00:20:30,270
How did you know my coffee order?

225
00:20:30,354 --> 00:20:31,521
I asked your friend.

226
00:20:33,232 --> 00:20:34,524
Well, this is for you.

227
00:20:37,319 --> 00:20:41,073
This has no caffeine in it,
just condensed milk and my sincerity.

228
00:20:48,288 --> 00:20:49,456
How is it?

229
00:20:51,166 --> 00:20:52,334
It's tasty.

230
00:21:05,889 --> 00:21:07,391
You're slightly late to work.

231
00:21:08,016 --> 00:21:09,393
Actually, I'm on time.

232
00:21:11,561 --> 00:21:13,021
Was I the only one who missed you?

233
00:21:13,647 --> 00:21:14,898
What do you mean?

234
00:21:15,691 --> 00:21:18,068
Why don't I camp out here tonight then?

235
00:21:18,235 --> 00:21:19,444
I'll stay up all night.

236
00:21:20,487 --> 00:21:22,489
-Can I join you?
-What?

237
00:21:24,950 --> 00:21:26,702
I've never slept in a tent before.

238
00:21:26,785 --> 00:21:28,203
Is that an American thing?

239
00:21:30,122 --> 00:21:32,457
FIRST BIRTHDAY

240
00:21:42,384 --> 00:21:44,594
Son, when did you get home?

241
00:21:44,678 --> 00:21:47,597
I told you to leave
the heavy lifting to me.

242
00:21:48,765 --> 00:21:50,392
Why would I bother my son who earns money

243
00:21:50,475 --> 00:21:52,519
when I have a husband
who carries heavy stones every day?

244
00:21:53,645 --> 00:21:55,272
I still have some muscles, you know.

245
00:21:57,482 --> 00:21:59,443
-Have you eaten?
-Yes.

246
00:21:59,985 --> 00:22:00,986
Mom,

247
00:22:01,236 --> 00:22:02,863
is my suit around?

248
00:22:02,946 --> 00:22:05,198
Your suit? Are you attending a wedding?

249
00:22:07,909 --> 00:22:10,078
Rather than be happy
to attend someone else's,

250
00:22:10,162 --> 00:22:12,205
you should think about
getting married yourself. It's here.

251
00:22:13,081 --> 00:22:14,708
Let me see if I had it dry-cleaned.

252
00:22:38,398 --> 00:22:40,358
What's with Ms. Sung today?

253
00:22:40,442 --> 00:22:43,236
I have a bad feeling about this.

254
00:22:43,320 --> 00:22:44,488
A bad feeling?

255
00:22:44,571 --> 00:22:47,699
Could Ms. Sung and Director Gold
have made up?

256
00:22:48,867 --> 00:22:50,077
No way.

257
00:22:50,285 --> 00:22:51,828
No way!

258
00:22:57,584 --> 00:22:58,835
Ms. Sung?

259
00:23:00,754 --> 00:23:03,381
-Yes, Director Gold.
-Let's begin the meeting.

260
00:23:03,590 --> 00:23:04,800
Shall we?

261
00:23:09,679 --> 00:23:11,098
Come on. Let's go.

262
00:23:15,852 --> 00:23:18,021
See? They're together again.

263
00:23:18,772 --> 00:23:20,690
Has the timer reset on the bomb then?

264
00:23:26,738 --> 00:23:30,117
Where are we with
Mr. Ahn's other artworks?

