Honey.

527
00:39:43,255 --> 00:39:45,174
Let's just think about Geon-u.

528
00:39:45,424 --> 00:39:46,634
Wherever you are right now,

529
00:39:47,301 --> 00:39:49,220
there will be a river nearby.

530
00:39:49,512 --> 00:39:50,471
A river?

531
00:39:51,389 --> 00:39:53,974
The river you'll soon be crossing.

532
00:39:54,141 --> 00:39:56,560
But I don't want to cross a river.

533
00:39:56,644 --> 00:39:57,853
Seung-min.

534
00:39:58,729 --> 00:40:00,106
Get over here right now.

535
00:40:00,981 --> 00:40:02,191
Right now!

536
00:40:10,157 --> 00:40:11,575
My gosh.

537
00:40:19,542 --> 00:40:22,586
Seon-ju, calm down and hear me out first.

538
00:40:22,837 --> 00:40:25,714
They promised to transfer me
to a variety show if I did this.

539
00:40:25,798 --> 00:40:27,800
So I had no choice but to do it.

540
00:40:28,217 --> 00:40:30,636
You also wanted me
to work on variety shows.

541
00:40:30,719 --> 00:40:32,972
I told you to work on variety shows,
not sell out your own wife.

542
00:40:33,055 --> 00:40:35,015
What are you talking about?
I didn't sell you out.

543
00:40:35,099 --> 00:40:36,767
-Ju-hyeok.
-Yes?

544
00:40:36,851 --> 00:40:38,477
-Lock the doors.
-Seon-ju.

545
00:40:38,561 --> 00:40:39,562
Ms. Lee.

546
00:40:39,645 --> 00:40:42,940
I'm going to become a widow today.

547
00:40:44,233 --> 00:40:45,734
Get over here!

548
00:40:47,361 --> 00:40:49,071
-Stop her!
-Get out of my way!

549
00:40:51,657 --> 00:40:52,950
Get over here!

550
00:40:54,118 --> 00:40:55,536
Gosh, no.

551
00:40:56,787 --> 00:40:58,831
Just take this bag back and leave!

552
00:40:59,540 --> 00:41:01,250
Seon-ju, I'm sorry.

553
00:41:03,711 --> 00:41:05,546
It must've been quite windy.

554
00:41:05,629 --> 00:41:07,256
-You have an eyelash here.
-What?

555
00:41:08,090 --> 00:41:09,967
Right there. It's a little to the side.

556
00:41:10,050 --> 00:41:11,177
-Right next to your eye.
-Here?

557
00:41:11,260 --> 00:41:12,344
Yes.

558
00:41:12,887 --> 00:41:14,722
No, not there. I'll do it for you.

559
00:41:19,727 --> 00:41:21,145
Don't do that.

560
00:41:29,069 --> 00:41:30,237
Okay, I'll stop.

561
00:41:54,136 --> 00:41:56,222
Let's go on a river cruise next time.

562
00:41:57,431 --> 00:42:00,684
Sure, let's do everything we can in Seoul.

563
00:42:02,436 --> 00:42:03,604
Just a second.

564
00:42:06,690 --> 00:42:08,275
Duk-mi, did you get off work?

565
00:42:08,359 --> 00:42:09,693
When are you planning to come home?

566
00:42:10,277 --> 00:42:11,529
Who is it?

567
00:42:11,904 --> 00:42:13,614
It's Eun-gi. He wants to know
if I got off work.

568
00:42:16,617 --> 00:42:18,035
You and Mr. Nam

569
00:42:18,953 --> 00:42:20,704
must be really close.

570
00:42:20,788 --> 00:42:22,039
Close?

571
00:42:25,292 --> 00:42:26,627
Why are you laughing?

572
00:42:27,503 --> 00:42:30,631
I never really thought
of our relationship that way.

573
00:42:30,714 --> 00:42:32,007
You're that close?

574
00:42:32,967 --> 00:42:35,886
Do you remember Editor Nam,
the woman who interviewed you?

575
00:42:35,970 --> 00:42:37,596
She's Eun-gi's mother.

576
00:42:37,721 --> 00:42:39,848
She and my mom first met
at an OB-GYN clinic.

577
00:42:39,932 --> 00:42:41,809
But Editor Nam had something
personal going on,

578
00:42:41,892 --> 00:42:45,729
so my mom started raising me
and Eun-gi like twins.

579
00:42:46,647 --> 00:42:48,983
He's like family to me.

580
00:42:51,318 --> 00:42:53,696
Do you think Mr. Nam

581
00:42:55,155 --> 00:42:56,699
also thinks that way?

582
00:42:59,702 --> 00:43:01,620
He might think differently.

583
00:43:02,621 --> 00:43:04,456
He might have feelings for you.

584
00:43:08,836 --> 00:43:12,006
A lot of people told me that
ever since we were students.

585
00:43:12,381 --> 00:43:15,134
We went to a co-ed school.

586
00:43:15,801 --> 00:43:19,013
Every time anyone said that,
Eun-gi and I got into a huge fight.

587
00:43:19,722 --> 00:43:22,349
But we're really like siblings.

588
00:43:22,433 --> 00:43:24,018
No, more like brothers.

589
00:43:24,518 --> 00:43:26,103
Or maybe sisters.

590
00:43:26,437 --> 00:43:28,522
He might feel differently
from how he did when he was young.

591
00:43:29,398 --> 00:43:31,817
There are times when people
take a while to realize their feelings.

592
00:43:34,403 --> 00:43:35,613
Director Gold.

593
00:43:37,406 --> 00:43:40,909
By any chance, are you doubting
my relationship with Eun-gi?

594
00:43:42,411 --> 00:43:44,163
I don't doubt you.

595
00:43:45,914 --> 00:43:49,627
I'm saying that he's always next to you,
so you might not know.

596
00:43:51,754 --> 00:43:53,005
What about you?

597
00:43:57,593 --> 00:44:00,804
I'm talking about Ms. Choi.
You two are really close.

598
00:44:01,889 --> 00:44:03,515
When it comes to Da-in,

599
00:44:05,476 --> 00:44:08,228
I can't say we're close,
but I do like her.

600
00:44:08,937 --> 00:44:10,022
What?

601
00:44:10,105 --> 00:44:12,149
I like her competence as an artist,

602
00:44:12,608 --> 00:44:14,693
and I like her works.

603
00:44:15,611 --> 00:44:17,571
And Da-in trusts me as a director

604
00:44:17,655 --> 00:44:19,865
and an artist.

605
00:44:20,658 --> 00:44:23,702
Do you think Ms. Choi feels the same way?

606
00:44:28,916 --> 00:44:30,334
That might not be the case.

607
00:44:55,150 --> 00:44:56,318
Duk-mi.

608
00:44:58,237 --> 00:44:59,446
As you already know,

609
00:45:00,030 --> 00:45:03,075
my lifetime goal was to win
a gold medal in the Olympics.

610
00:45:04,368 --> 00:45:05,953
But now, my goal

611
00:45:08,288 --> 00:45:09,498
is you.

612
00:45:12,084 --> 00:45:13,710
I want to buy you delicious stuff,

613
00:45:14,795 --> 00:45:16,964
make you laugh, make you happy,

614
00:45:17,339 --> 00:45:20,426
protect you, and take you home every day.

615
00:45:21,635 --> 00:45:25,055
I may have retired
as an Olympic silver medalist,

616
00:45:28,642 --> 00:45:31,186
but I won't ever retire
when it comes to fighting for you.

617
00:45:36,275 --> 00:45:37,734
I like you, Duk-mi.

618
00:45:43,323 --> 00:45:44,783
I can do this.

619
00:45:58,172 --> 00:45:59,506
Go home safely.

620
00:46:04,261 --> 00:46:05,512
Director Gold?

621
00:46:05,929 --> 00:46:09,391
You know I don't like letting go
of someone's hand.

622
00:46:14,855 --> 00:46:16,648
Why don't you just take me inside as well?

623
00:46:18,400 --> 00:46:20,569
How about just my hand, then?

624
00:46:22,237 --> 00:46:23,822
Just your hand?

625
00:46:25,908 --> 00:46:28,869
You're saying something really scary
with a smile.

626
00:46:29,745 --> 00:46:30,871
Goodnight, then.

627
00:46:32,247 --> 00:46:33,373
Goodnight.

628
00:47:09,952 --> 00:47:10,953
Ms. Sung.

629
00:47:21,296 --> 00:47:22,548
What...

630
00:47:48,657 --> 00:47:49,866
Hold still.

631
00:48:04,089 --> 00:48:05,465
What's this?

632
00:48:05,757 --> 00:48:07,926
I was going to give it to you that night,

633
00:48:09,261 --> 00:48:10,804
but you dumped me.

634
00:48:11,263 --> 00:48:14,182
Your actions upset me quite a lot.

635
00:48:14,349 --> 00:48:15,392
Did I mention that?

636
00:48:15,475 --> 00:48:17,519
I didn't dump you.

637
00:48:19,229 --> 00:48:20,439
You know that.

638
00:48:24,985 --> 00:48:26,028
It's pretty.

639
00:50:25,897 --> 00:50:30,152
FIRST DATE WITH LION

640
00:50:51,631 --> 00:50:52,799
Duk-mi.

641
00:50:54,009 --> 00:50:55,093
Duk-mi!

642
00:50:56,803 --> 00:50:57,971
Gosh, Eun-gi.

643
00:51:06,104 --> 00:51:07,439
I like you.

644
00:51:08,523 --> 00:51:09,775
I like you, Duk-mi.

645
00:51:10,484 --> 00:51:11,443
I...

646
00:51:11,860 --> 00:51:15,238
I'm sorry.
I read your text but didn't reply.

647
00:51:15,322 --> 00:51:18,533
I prepared these for you,
so please take what you need.

648
00:51:18,700 --> 00:51:19,701
Here you go.

649
00:51:24,456 --> 00:51:25,582
Are you mad?

650
00:51:27,709 --> 00:51:29,878
Then what's with that face?
Smile, you jerk.

651
00:51:29,961 --> 00:51:32,923
-Smile! Right now!
-I'm not angry.

652
00:51:33,965 --> 00:51:34,966
Right?

653
00:51:35,550 --> 00:51:36,927
But what's with the suit?

654
00:51:40,222 --> 00:51:41,598
-Duk-mi.
-Yes?

655
00:51:43,517 --> 00:51:45,018
When we were born,

656
00:51:47,395 --> 00:51:50,607
if my mom hadn't tried
to abandon me at the hospital...

657
00:51:50,690 --> 00:51:53,235
You knew? Since when?

658
00:51:53,318 --> 00:51:54,694
When I joined the national team.

659
00:51:55,153 --> 00:51:56,905
Editor Nam got drunk
and spilled everything.

660
00:51:57,781 --> 00:52:00,450
I thought she only did that with me.

661
00:52:02,536 --> 00:52:05,038
Anyway, I doubt she really meant it.

662
00:52:06,122 --> 00:52:09,501
That's why Mom was able to catch her.

663
00:52:09,584 --> 00:52:11,336
If Editor Nam were serious
about running away,

664
00:52:11,419 --> 00:52:13,713
she wouldn't have
blindly trusted a stranger.

665
00:52:15,298 --> 00:52:17,717
I'm sure she was just terrified.

666
00:52:19,261 --> 00:52:21,596
I understand since she was
younger than we are now.

667
00:52:23,306 --> 00:52:24,808
Editor Nam told me

668
00:52:25,892 --> 00:52:27,102
to be good.

669
00:52:30,564 --> 00:52:34,568
I should be good to your mom,
your dad, and you, too.

670
00:52:37,362 --> 00:52:38,697
You're my family.

671
00:52:38,780 --> 00:52:40,615
Of course we are.

672
00:52:40,824 --> 00:52:42,450
-But Duk-mi.
-Yes?

673
00:52:44,870 --> 00:52:46,204
I...

674
00:52:47,497 --> 00:52:48,707
You see...

675
00:52:50,876 --> 00:52:53,003
-I'd like to--
-Seon-ju?

676
00:52:53,253 --> 00:52:55,672
-Seon-ju?
-What are you doing here so late?

677
00:52:57,674 --> 00:52:59,009
Something happened, didn't it?

678
00:53:01,303 --> 00:53:03,221
-Duk-mi.
-Yes?

679
00:53:03,305 --> 00:53:04,639
I'm going back.

680
00:53:04,723 --> 00:53:06,808
-To where?
-To being single again.

681
00:53:31,458 --> 00:53:32,626
EX-HUSBAND

682
00:53:38,757 --> 00:53:39,883
Seon-ju.

683
00:53:40,091 --> 00:53:42,052
The show was going to be made
one way or another.

684
00:53:42,177 --> 00:53:44,971
Isn't it better for it to have been
directed by him...

685
00:53:47,307 --> 00:53:49,434
Forget I said anything. Drink up.

686
00:53:52,395 --> 00:53:53,897
-Duk-mi.
-Yes?

687
00:53:54,314 --> 00:53:56,441
Don't you ever get married.

688
00:53:57,108 --> 00:53:59,319
No, don't even bother dating.

689
00:53:59,527 --> 00:54:00,820
Just stay single.

690
00:54:00,904 --> 00:54:03,156
You're never any help, are you?

691
00:54:04,407 --> 00:54:05,700
Jerk.

692
00:54:08,787 --> 00:54:09,913
MR. KANG

693
00:54:10,288 --> 00:54:11,623
If it's Seung-min, don't answer.

694
00:54:12,290 --> 00:54:15,126
-He'll be worried, so--
-I'll kill myself if you do.

695
00:54:15,293 --> 00:54:16,419
I'll kill myself!

696
00:54:17,462 --> 00:54:19,589
-I'm leaving.
-No, wait.

697
00:54:19,673 --> 00:54:21,091
Stay here.

698
00:54:22,968 --> 00:54:25,011
Don't answer him.

699
00:54:25,345 --> 00:54:26,888
Let's turn off all our phones.

700
00:54:27,263 --> 00:54:30,016
I can't believe that jerk!

701
00:54:30,100 --> 00:54:32,477
Let him worry about you all night.

702
00:54:34,479 --> 00:54:35,647
How's that?

703
00:54:45,615 --> 00:54:48,576
Seon-ju, drink up. I'm just as upset, too.

704
00:54:48,660 --> 00:54:51,496
-Let's get wasted.
-Sure thing.

705
00:54:51,997 --> 00:54:54,374
We have lots of time to drink.

706
00:54:54,833 --> 00:54:55,959
You wench.

707
00:55:20,275 --> 00:55:21,901
I can't get it out of my head.

708
00:55:33,496 --> 00:55:35,790
SUNG DUK-MI

709
00:55:44,549 --> 00:55:45,759
What?

710
00:55:48,428 --> 00:55:49,596
Why?

711
00:56:00,398 --> 00:56:01,316
It's seven o'clock.

712
00:56:02,192 --> 00:56:04,319
It's the perfect time
to go see my girlfriend.

713
00:56:14,204 --> 00:56:16,372
-Mr. Kim.
-Where are you going today?

714
00:56:16,456 --> 00:56:19,000
-Sangam-dong.
-Why don't you go to work a bit late?

715
00:56:19,334 --> 00:56:20,877
You should get some rest on closing days.

716
00:56:20,960 --> 00:56:23,171
Mr. Kim, did you already forget?

717
00:56:23,254 --> 00:56:25,507
My real job is fangirling.

718
00:56:26,216 --> 00:56:28,426
-Here.
-I'll see you later.

719
00:56:47,570 --> 00:56:49,030
Oh, my. Director Eom.

720
00:56:54,202 --> 00:56:55,829
Hey!

721
00:57:01,751 --> 00:57:02,877
Mom.

722
00:57:22,021 --> 00:57:23,273
Duk-mi, where are you going?

723
00:57:23,356 --> 00:57:25,900
How could you get drunk like that, too?

724
00:57:29,362 --> 00:57:30,947
It's been a long time since I drank.

725
00:57:32,157 --> 00:57:34,117
-Where are you going?
-Me?

726
00:57:34,451 --> 00:57:36,494
To shoot pictures of Si-an
on his way to work.

727
00:57:38,246 --> 00:57:40,331
Gosh, you're unbelievable.

728
00:57:43,543 --> 00:57:45,003
You like fangirling more than breakfast?

729
00:57:46,671 --> 00:57:47,797
This is my breakfast.

730
00:57:48,381 --> 00:57:50,633
Goodness. Will this be enough?

731
00:57:50,717 --> 00:57:52,010
The camera is heavy, too.

732
00:57:52,093 --> 00:57:53,803
This will be enough. I'm full.

733
00:57:54,596 --> 00:57:56,848
Wake Seon-ju up before you go. See you.

734
00:58:06,816 --> 00:58:08,109
Wait for me.

735
00:58:29,214 --> 00:58:31,508
Do you want to continue fangirling
after what happened to Seon-ju?

736
00:58:31,674 --> 00:58:34,093
At times like this, I have to
continue fangirling consistently

737
00:58:34,177 --> 00:58:36,179
so Seon-ju forgives her husband.

738
00:58:37,138 --> 00:58:38,348
How logical.

739
00:58:38,681 --> 00:58:40,225
You must've studied hard
when you were a kid.

740
00:58:40,308 --> 00:58:42,894
Don't you remember?
I solved all your questions for you.

741
00:58:42,977 --> 00:58:45,021
-You did.
-Let's go.

742
00:59:11,464 --> 00:59:14,509
Hey. Did something
really happen yesterday?

743
00:59:15,260 --> 00:59:16,719
-What's wrong?
-It's Lion.

744
00:59:34,904 --> 00:59:36,114
Ms. Sung.

745
00:59:40,034 --> 00:59:41,494
Director Gold.

746
00:59:42,287 --> 00:59:43,788
Did you come without even making plans?

747
00:59:44,706 --> 00:59:45,915
Today is...

748
00:59:47,375 --> 00:59:48,543
Come back next time.

749
01:00:02,181 --> 01:00:04,350
I want to speak with Duk-mi.

750
01:00:13,484 --> 01:00:14,694
Duk-mi

751
01:00:16,321 --> 01:00:17,572
didn't wash her face.

752
01:00:18,323 --> 01:00:21,200
I don't think she feels comfortable
seeing you right now.

753
01:00:29,500 --> 01:00:32,003
I said I want to speak with Duk-mi.

754
01:00:37,425 --> 01:00:39,802
Duk-mi says she doesn't want
to speak with you.

755
01:00:42,847 --> 01:00:43,973
Duk-mi

756
01:00:45,183 --> 01:00:46,392
is my girlfriend.

757
01:00:55,151 --> 01:00:56,903
So this is between her and me.

758
01:00:57,612 --> 01:00:59,947
It's none of your business.

759
01:01:03,493 --> 01:01:04,994
Why isn't it my business?

760
01:01:07,497 --> 01:01:08,915
She's the woman I like.

761
01:01:16,881 --> 01:01:20,093
Duk-mi doesn't want herself
to be seen right now.

762
01:01:21,803 --> 01:01:23,054
By you, Director Gold.

763
01:01:25,640 --> 01:01:27,642
If you really care for Duk-mi,

764
01:01:29,060 --> 01:01:30,269
please leave for now.

765
01:01:50,081 --> 01:01:51,999
Come out, Ms. Sung.

766
01:02:04,887 --> 01:02:06,139
It's okay.

767
01:02:10,893 --> 01:02:11,978
The Road to Si-an.

768
01:03:10,912 --> 01:03:13,498
Why did you bring me to your place
to fight?

769
01:03:13,581 --> 01:03:14,957
Is it a home game or what?

770
01:03:15,041 --> 01:03:16,751
Ryan? Ms. Sung?

771
01:03:16,834 --> 01:03:18,085
Why didn't you tell me?

772
01:03:18,169 --> 01:03:20,379
Because she doesn't know
how you feel about her.

773
01:03:20,588 --> 01:03:23,633
Did Mr. Nam sleep at your place
last night?

774
01:03:23,800 --> 01:03:26,969
-And as for Eun-gi--
-He likes you.

775
01:03:27,178 --> 01:03:30,139
Right now, you're not family nor a friend
to me. You're a woman.

776
01:03:30,223 --> 01:03:32,600
No matter how long it takes, I can wait.

777
01:03:33,100 --> 01:03:34,393
Teach me too.

778
01:03:34,894 --> 01:03:37,021
So I want to be your fanboy too.

779
01:03:37,313 --> 01:03:39,524
Subtitle translation by Ju-young Park

